    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 27 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A resistor of resistance, R is connected across a cell. If the terminal p.d of the cell is reduced to one-quarter of its e.m.f, express the internal resistance, r of the cell in terms of R.",
      "type": "subJective"
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "r = 3R"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Internal Resistance Derivation</h3><p>From the terminal voltage condition:</p><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'><strong>V = ε - Ir = ε/4</strong><br>Current I = ε/(R + r)<br>Substituting: ε/4 = ε - [ε/(R + r)]r<br>Solving gives: <strong>r = 3R</strong></p></div>"
    },
